  // across different data types and distributions. A compile-time check
  // dispatches to the most suitable algorithm.

  // For standard integer types, a sort-based approach using parallel radix sort
  // is often the fastest. Radix sort (parlay::integer_sort) has linear-time
  // complexity and exhibits excellent cache locality due to its streaming memory
  // access patterns. This can outperform the hash-based approach, which has
  // more random memory accesses, especially on inputs with a high number of
