// their active neighbors are added to the independent set. These vertices and
// all their neighbors are then removed from the graph, and the process
// repeats on the remaining active vertices. This lock-free approach avoids
// the high contention and spinning of lock-based alternatives and is highly
// parallel. The expected number of rounds is logarithmic in the number of
// vertices, leading to an efficient and scalable algorithm.
parlay::sequence<char> maximalIndependentSet(const Graph &G) {
